markets.title: Will **New York** (excluding NYC) average less than 3,000 new COVID-19 cases per day by March?
markets.subtitle: <3K
markets.rules_primary: If the seven-day moving average of new COVID-19 cases for New York (excluding NYC) is below 3,000 for a single day between Issuance and March 01, 2022, then the market resolves to Yes.
markets.rules_secondary: Note that this Contract may close and expire early. It will expire the first 10:00 AM following the CDC reporting the event has occured, the first 10:00 AM following data being released for March 01, 2022, or 10:00 AM on March 08, 2022.

markets.title: Will **New York (excluding NYC) average more than 50,000 new COVID-19 cases** per day by February 1?
markets.subtitle: >50K
markets.rules_primary: If the seven-day moving average of new COVID-19 cases for New York (excluding NYC) is above 50,000 for a single day between Issuance and February 01, 2022, then the market resolves to Yes.
markets.rules_secondary: Note that this Contract may close and expire early. It will expire the first 10:00 AM following the CDC reporting the event has occured, the first 10:00 AM following data being released for February 01, 2022, or 10:00 AM on February 04, 2022.

markets.title: Will New York (excluding NYC) have **peak new average COVID-19 cases** by the end of the year?
markets.rules_primary: If the seven-day moving average of new COVID-19 cases for New York (excluding NYC) is above 10,485 for a single day between Issuance and December 31, 2021, then the market resolves to Yes.
markets.rules_secondary: Note that this Contract may close and expire early. It will expire the first 10:00 AM following the CDC reporting the event has occured, the first 10:00 AM following data being released for December 31, 2021, or 10:00 AM on January 07, 2022.
